[{"id":"VR614535","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a system of two blocks arranged vertically and connected to one another by a vertical string. The top block has mass m, and the bottom block has mass 2 m. The two blocks are moving vertically downward.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR614535.g02.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is attached to a block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 m\"><math alttext=\"2 m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> by a vertical string, as shown. At the instant shown, the blocks are freely falling near the Earthâ€™s surface. Which of the following correctly indicates the acceleration of the block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 m\"><math alttext=\"2 m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> and provides a valid justification?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR614535_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Equal to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g\"><math alttext=\"g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the other block is also in free-fall and therefore the tension in the string is zero.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Equal to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g\"><math alttext=\"g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the force exerted by the string on the bottom block is equal and opposite to the weight of the bottom block.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g\"><math alttext=\"g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the string exerts an upward tension force on the bottom block.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g\"><math alttext=\"g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the mass of the block is less than the inertial mass of the two-block system.</p>"],"answer":0}]